div.p:
The Thebans were wont to make the Statues of their Judges without Hands;
               Plut. de Iſid. & Oſir. to note they ſhould take no Bribes: but he cannot poſſibly be a good Judge, who (as it is ſaid of the Sword-Fiſh) is without Heart; who wants Courage and Reſolution to Execute Juſtice and

Judgment. A Judge muſt have an Eagles Eye, and a Lyons Heart: He muſt have a Quickneſs of Sight to detect mens Crimes, and a Courage ſufficient to condemn the Guilty:
